1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:03,400
你厨房里最便宜的东西可能是盐
You might think the cheapest thing in your kitchen is salt

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:04,966
一袋盐几块钱
A bag of salt costs just a few yuan

3
00:00:05,133 --> 00:00:08,500
便宜到你买它的时候几乎不会思考
It is so cheap you barely think about buying it

4
00:00:08,733 --> 00:00:09,933
但你有没有想过
But have you ever wondered

5
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:13,233
古代很多帝国最稳定的钱袋子
For many ancient empires the most reliable money maker

6
00:00:13,233 --> 00:00:14,300
恰恰就是盐
Was exactly salt

7
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:15,533
不是黄金
Not gold

8
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:16,733
不是土地
Not land

9
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:17,933
不是丝绸
Not silk

10
00:00:18,166 --> 00:00:20,133
而是你每天炒菜时
But those tiny white grains

11
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:22,900
随手撒进去的那一点白色颗粒
You toss into your cooking every day

12
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:24,400
更反常识的是
What is even more counterintuitive

13
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:27,833
盐之所以能赚钱不是因为它贵
Salt made money not because it was expensive

14
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:29,800
恰恰是因为它太普通
But precisely because it was so ordinary

15
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,700
普通到每个人都需要
Ordinary enough that everyone needed it

16
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,833
普通到每一天都要用
Ordinary enough that everyone used it daily

17
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,766
普通到你离不开它
Ordinary enough that you could not live without it

18
00:00:35,766 --> 00:00:37,933
却很少会为了它讨价还价
But rarely bothered to bargain over it

19
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:40,000
这就是盐最可怕的地方
This is what makes salt so powerful

20
00:00:40,166 --> 00:00:41,366
它不是调味品
It is not just a seasoning

21
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:43,333
它是古代政府手里
It was the ancient government

22
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:45,200
最完美的一台印钞机
The most perfect money printing machine

23
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:48,166
今天这条视频我们就用一袋盐
In this video we will use a bag of salt

24
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:49,566
讲透三个问题
To explain three things

25
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:51,633
为什么最不起眼的东西
Why the most overlooked things

26
00:00:51,900 --> 00:00:53,600
反而最容易被定价
Are the easiest to price

27
00:00:53,766 --> 00:00:55,900
为什么古代国家喜欢控制盐
Why ancient states loved controlling salt

28
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:59,000
以及在 AI 时代谁掌握了新的盐
And in the AI age whoever controls the new salt

29
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,333
谁就掌握了普通人的生活入口
Controls the gateway to ordinary people

30
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:02,766
先别急着想帝国
Do not rush to think about empires

31
00:01:02,933 --> 00:01:04,366
你先想自己的厨房
Think about your own kitchen first

32
00:01:04,566 --> 00:01:07,233
如果今天猪肉涨价你可以少吃肉
If pork prices go up you can eat less meat

33
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:10,133
如果奶茶涨价你可以不喝
If bubble tea gets expensive you can skip it

34
00:01:10,366 --> 00:01:12,966
如果手机涨价你可以晚一年换
If phones get pricier you can wait a year to upgrade

35
00:01:13,166 --> 00:01:14,166
但盐呢
But what about salt

36
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:16,700
你不会因为盐涨了几毛钱
You would not stop eating salt

37
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:17,933
就从此不吃盐
Just because it went up a few cents

38
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:20,700
这就是经济学里一个很重要的概念
This is an important concept in economics

39
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:22,166
需求价格弹性
Price elasticity of demand

40
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:23,566
翻成人话就是
In plain English it means

41
00:01:23,766 --> 00:01:26,500
东西涨价以后你还买不买
When something gets more expensive do you still buy it

42
00:01:26,633 --> 00:01:28,900
奶茶涨价你可以不买
If bubble tea goes up you can stop buying it

43
00:01:29,133 --> 00:01:31,366
电影票涨价你可以不看
If movie tickets cost more you can skip the movies

44
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:34,966
但盐这种东西涨一点你还是要买
But with something like salt even if it goes up a bit you still buy it

45
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:36,900
因为它不是享受型消费
Because it is not a luxury

46
00:01:37,033 --> 00:01:38,700
它是生存型消费
It is a necessity

47
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:40,633
你可能不懂经济学公式
You might not know economic formulas

48
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,433
但你每天买菜的时候
But every time you go grocery shopping

49
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:44,300
已经在用这个公式了
You are already using this formula

50
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:47,800
越是可有可无的东西消费者越敏感
The more dispensable something is the more sensitive consumers are

51
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:51,500
越是离不开的东西消费者越没得选
The more essential something is the less choice consumers have

52
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:53,400
这就是盐的第一层秘密
This is the first secret of salt

53
00:01:53,566 --> 00:01:55,100
它小到没人重视
It is so small nobody pays attention

54
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,100
但它刚需到人人都要
But so essential everyone needs it

55
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,300
你想象一下
Imagine this

56
00:01:58,433 --> 00:02:00,733
如果一个古代政府想收税
If an ancient government wanted to collect taxes

57
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:02,933
它可以挨家挨户去查田地
It could go door to door checking farmland

58
00:02:03,133 --> 00:02:05,133
也可以盯着商人一笔一笔做账
Or watch every single merchant transaction

59
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:06,600
但这些都很难
But all of that is really hard

60
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:08,400
农民会瞒产量
Farmers would hide their yields

61
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:10,100
商人会藏利润
Merchants would hide their profits

62
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,833
地方官会层层截留
Local officials would skim at every level

63
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,166
可盐不一样
But salt is different

64
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,900
盐的生产地点相对集中
Salt production sites are relatively concentrated

65
00:02:16,133 --> 00:02:19,933
盐井 盐湖 盐场 都不是你家后院随便能变出来的
Salt wells salt lakes salt pans you cannot just make them in your backyard

66
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:23,700
只要国家控制了产地 运输和销售
As long as the state controls production transport and sales

67
00:02:23,833 --> 00:02:25,900
它就不用天天追着每个人收税
It does not need to chase everyone down for taxes

68
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,966
它只要在你买盐的时候
It just needs to collect when you buy salt

69
00:02:28,166 --> 00:02:30,200
顺手收走一小部分
And take a small cut along the way

70
00:02:30,366 --> 00:02:31,933
你不知不觉就交了钱
You pay without even realizing it

71
00:02:32,133 --> 00:02:33,833
这比直接收税温柔得多
This is much gentler than direct taxation

72
00:02:34,133 --> 00:02:35,233
也隐蔽得多
And much more hidden too

73
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:37,400
你以为你在买调味品
You think you are buying seasoning

74
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:39,566
其实你在给国家财政充值
Actually you are funding the national treasury

75
00:02:39,633 --> 00:02:42,333
最好的税不是让你痛到反抗
The best tax is not one that hurts enough to make you rebel

76
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:44,900
而是让你习惯到忘记
But one you get so used to that you forget about it

77
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:46,966
盐为什么能撑起帝国
Why could salt sustain an empire

78
00:02:47,166 --> 00:02:49,700
因为它踩中了商业里最硬的规律
Because it hit the hardest rule in business

79
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,433
高频 刚需 低替代
High frequency essential low substitutability

80
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:53,433
这三个词放在今天
These three words today

81
00:02:53,566 --> 00:02:56,300
就是所有平台都想要的梦中情人
Are the dream of every platform

82
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,733
你每天打开微信
You open WeChat every day

83
00:02:57,966 --> 00:02:59,300
每天刷短视频
You scroll short videos every day

84
00:02:59,966 --> 00:03:00,900
每天点外卖
You order takeout every day

85
00:03:01,133 --> 00:03:02,933
每天用搜索和 AI
You use search and AI every day

86
00:03:03,366 --> 00:03:04,533
逻辑都一样
The logic is the same

87
00:03:04,766 --> 00:03:07,366
只要一件东西变成你的日常入口
Once something becomes your daily gateway

88
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:09,533
它就不再只是一个产品
It is no longer just a product

89
00:03:09,700 --> 00:03:11,433
它会变成一条收费通道
It becomes a toll channel

90
00:03:11,633 --> 00:03:14,500
盐在古代是嘴巴的入口
Salt in ancient times was the gateway to the mouth

91
00:03:14,633 --> 00:03:17,833
平台在今天是注意力的入口
Platforms today are the gateway to attention

92
00:03:18,033 --> 00:03:22,033
AI 在明天可能是知识和决策的入口
AI tomorrow could be the gateway to knowledge and decisions

93
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,166
你看懂盐
Understand salt

94
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:26,733
就看懂了所有入口生意的本质
And you understand the essence of all gateway businesses

95
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:29,000
把镜头拉回两千多年前
Pull the camera back over two thousand years

96
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:31,500
汉武帝时期汉朝很强
During the Han Dynasty Emperor Wu the Han was very powerful

97
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:32,833
强到什么程度
How powerful

98
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:34,133
北边打匈奴
Fighting the Xiongnu in the north

99
00:03:34,433 --> 00:03:35,566
西边通西域
Opening the Western Regions in the west

100
00:03:35,766 --> 00:03:38,533
修路 养马 打仗 赏赐 管理边疆
Building roads raising horses fighting wars rewarding officials managing frontiers

101
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:39,766
这些都要钱
All of that cost money

102
00:03:39,966 --> 00:03:41,600
而且不是小钱
And not just a little

103
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:44,533
帝国越扩张财政压力越大
The more the empire expanded the greater the financial pressure

104
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:47,400
你可以把它想象成一家高速扩张的公司
You can think of it as a fast growing company

105
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:49,133
办公室越开越多
Opening more and more offices

106
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:50,933
员工越招越多
Hiring more and more employees

107
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:52,400
市场越打越大
Expanding into more and more markets

108
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:53,900
看起来很风光
It looks impressive

109
00:03:54,033 --> 00:03:55,833
但现金流天天在流血
But cash flow is bleeding every day

110
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,633
这时候老板会盯上什么
What would the boss focus on then

111
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:01,100
不会先盯上员工偶尔买一次的礼品
Not the occasional gifts employees buy

112
00:04:01,233 --> 00:04:04,700
他会盯上所有人每天都要用的基础服务
He would focus on the basic services everyone uses every day

113
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:05,966
汉武帝做的事
What Emperor Wu did

114
00:04:05,966 --> 00:04:08,900
就是把盐和铁收归国家控制
Was to bring salt and iron under state control

115
00:04:08,966 --> 00:04:11,733
这就是历史上很有名的盐铁专营
This is the famous Salt and Iron Monopoly in history

116
00:04:11,966 --> 00:04:13,533
盐负责日常消费
Salt handled daily consumption

117
00:04:13,733 --> 00:04:16,000
铁负责生产工具和兵器
Iron handled production tools and weapons

118
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:17,366
一个管嘴巴
One controlled the mouth

119
00:04:17,566 --> 00:04:18,833
一个管生产
One controlled production

120
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,566
这两个东西被控制住
With both of these under control

121
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:22,233
国家就有了稳定现金流
The state had a stable cash flow

122
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,633
后来到了前 81 年
Later in 81 BC

123
00:04:24,633 --> 00:04:26,700
汉朝还专门开过一次大辩论
The Han Dynasty held a major debate

124
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:29,633
主题就是盐铁政策到底要不要继续
On whether the salt and iron policy should continue

125
00:04:29,966 --> 00:04:31,900
这场辩论后来被整理成盐铁论
This debate was compiled into the Discourses on Salt and Iron

126
00:04:32,033 --> 00:04:35,733
你可以把它理解成古代版的经济政策听证会
You can think of it as an ancient economic policy hearing

127
00:04:35,933 --> 00:04:36,766
一边说
One side argued

128
00:04:36,966 --> 00:04:38,433
国家不控制盐铁
Without state control of salt and iron

129
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:40,966
就没钱保边疆 平物价 管大局
There would be no money to defend borders stabilize prices and manage the big picture

130
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:42,133
另一边说
The other side argued

131
00:04:42,433 --> 00:04:45,500
国家垄断太多民间商人没有活力
Too much state monopoly kills private sector vitality

132
00:04:45,533 --> 00:04:46,966
老百姓负担太重
The burden on ordinary people is too heavy

133
00:04:47,166 --> 00:04:48,133
你发现没有
Have you noticed

134
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:49,766
两千多年前的人
People from over two thousand years ago

135
00:04:49,766 --> 00:04:52,033
已经在争今天还在争的问题
Were already debating the same issues we debate today

136
00:04:52,300 --> 00:04:54,500
国家应该多管一点还是少管一点
Should the state control more or less

137
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:57,833
市场自由重要还是财政安全重要
Is market freedom more important or fiscal security

138
00:04:58,100 --> 00:05:00,233
效率重要还是稳定重要
Is efficiency more important or stability

139
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,800
盐只是表面
Salt is just the surface

140
00:05:01,966 --> 00:05:04,100
背后争的是一个国家怎么拿钱
Behind it is a debate about how a state takes money

141
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:05,166
又怎么花钱
And how it spends it

142
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:06,533
如果你是普通人
If you are an ordinary person

143
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:08,300
你可能会天然讨厌垄断
You might naturally hate monopolies

144
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:11,233
因为垄断意味着价格不完全由你决定
Because monopoly means prices are not fully up to you

145
00:05:11,366 --> 00:05:14,166
但如果你是国家你会看到另一面
But if you are the state you see another side

146
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:15,333
边疆要守
Frontiers must be defended

147
00:05:15,533 --> 00:05:16,533
灾荒要救
Disasters must be relieved

148
00:05:16,766 --> 00:05:17,833
道路要修
Roads must be built

149
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:18,966
军队要养
Armies must be maintained

150
00:05:19,133 --> 00:05:21,900
这些公共成本总要有人买单
Someone has to pay for all these public costs

151
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:23,133
问题只是
The question is only

152
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,633
这个单是明着交
Do you pay it openly

153
00:05:25,766 --> 00:05:27,900
还是藏在盐价里交
Or is it hidden in the price of salt

154
00:05:28,166 --> 00:05:30,566
盐铁专营最厉害的地方就在这里
This is where the Salt and Iron Monopoly was most brilliant

155
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:33,800
它把财政问题包装成了日常消费
It turned a fiscal problem into everyday consumption

156
00:05:33,966 --> 00:05:35,000
你买一袋盐
You buy a bag of salt

157
00:05:35,166 --> 00:05:36,533
国家多一笔收入
The state gets more revenue

158
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:37,733
你吃一顿饭
You eat a meal

159
00:05:37,966 --> 00:05:39,600
帝国多一点续航
The empire gets more staying power

160
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:41,200
这听起来很夸张
This sounds exaggerated

161
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:43,033
但财政的本质
But the essence of fiscal policy

162
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:45,566
本来就不是一笔惊天动地的大钱
Is never about one earth shattering fortune

163
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:47,433
而是无数小钱
It is about countless small amounts

164
00:05:47,533 --> 00:05:49,366
稳定地流向同一个地方
Steadily flowing to the same place

165
00:05:49,433 --> 00:05:51,100
一个人一天只交一点
One person pays a little every day

166
00:05:51,233 --> 00:05:52,833
一千万人每天都交一点
Ten million people pay a little every day

167
00:05:53,033 --> 00:05:54,333
这就不是一点了
That is no longer a little

168
00:05:54,533 --> 00:05:55,433
这叫规模
That is scale

169
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:56,633
这叫现金流
That is cash flow

170
00:05:56,833 --> 00:05:58,300
这叫帝国的底气
That is the confidence of an empire

171
00:05:58,533 --> 00:05:59,333
所以你看
So you see

172
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,766
盐不是因为神秘才重要
Salt is not important because it is mysterious

173
00:06:01,966 --> 00:06:04,000
盐是因为普通才重要
Salt is important because it is ordinary

174
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:06,500
越普通越高频
The more ordinary the higher the frequency

175
00:06:06,766 --> 00:06:08,600
越高频越稳定
The higher the frequency the more stable

176
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:12,100
越稳定越适合被制度化
The more stable the easier to institutionalize

177
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:13,733
这就是第二层秘密
This is the second secret

178
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:16,800
能撑起大系统的往往不是爆款
What sustains a big system is usually not a blockbuster

179
00:06:16,933 --> 00:06:18,033
而是刚需
But a necessity

180
00:06:18,233 --> 00:06:19,533
爆款让人兴奋
Blockbusters get people excited

181
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:21,333
刚需让系统活下去
Necessities keep systems alive

182
00:06:21,566 --> 00:06:23,700
如果盐只是赚钱工具
If salt were just a money making tool

183
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,733
那故事还不够完整
The story would not be complete

184
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:27,700
真正有意思的是
What is really interesting

185
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:31,366
盐既能撑起帝国也能撬动帝国
Is that salt could both sustain and topple an empire

186
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:35,166
1930 年印度发生过一件很有名的事
In 1930 something famous happened in India

187
00:06:35,366 --> 00:06:37,133
甘地带着追随者
Gandhi led his followers

188
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:39,200
从阿默达巴德附近出发
From near Ahmedabad

189
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:41,100
一路走到海边的丹地
All the way to the coast at Dandi

190
00:06:41,233 --> 00:06:42,433
这就是盐进军
This was the Salt March

191
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,800
他们反抗的
What they were fighting against

192
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:46,000
不是一件听起来宏大的事
Was not something that sounds grand

193
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,233
不是王位
Not a throne

194
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:48,366
不是军队
Not an army

195
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,400
不是石油
Not oil

196
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,400
而是盐
But salt

197
00:06:50,633 --> 00:06:54,533
当时英国殖民政府控制印度的盐生产和销售
At that time the British colonial government controlled Indias salt production and sales

198
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:56,933
印度人不能随便自己制盐
Indians could not freely make their own salt

199
00:06:57,033 --> 00:07:00,500
一个靠海的国家普通人面对海水
A country surrounded by sea where ordinary people faced the ocean

200
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:02,333
却不能自由得到盐
Yet could not freely obtain salt

201
00:07:02,533 --> 00:07:03,833
你想想这个画面
Imagine that scene

202
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,233
海就在眼前
The sea is right there

203
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:06,633
盐就在水里
The salt is in the water

204
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:09,400
但制度告诉你这不是你的
But the system tells you this is not yours

205
00:07:09,566 --> 00:07:12,700
这个时候盐就不只是商品了
At this point salt was no longer just a commodity

206
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,433
它变成了一种羞辱感
It became a sense of humiliation

207
00:07:14,633 --> 00:07:16,433
为什么甘地选盐
Why did Gandhi choose salt

208
00:07:16,700 --> 00:07:18,166
因为盐太普通了
Because salt was so ordinary

209
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:20,333
普通到每个印度人都懂
Ordinary enough that every Indian understood

210
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:21,333
农民懂
Farmers understood

211
00:07:21,533 --> 00:07:22,500
工人懂
Workers understood

212
00:07:22,766 --> 00:07:23,600
老人懂
The elderly understood

213
00:07:23,766 --> 00:07:24,766
孩子也懂
Even children understood

214
00:07:24,933 --> 00:07:26,800
如果他讲复杂的宪政理论
If he had talked about complex constitutional theory

215
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:27,800
很多人听不懂
Many people would not have understood

216
00:07:27,933 --> 00:07:30,566
如果他讲贸易 关税 殖民财政
If he had talked about trade tariffs colonial fiscal policy

217
00:07:31,233 --> 00:07:32,833
普通人可能没感觉
Ordinary people might not have felt anything

218
00:07:33,033 --> 00:07:34,033
但他讲盐
But when he talked about salt

219
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:35,600
所有人立刻明白
Everyone immediately understood

220
00:07:35,766 --> 00:07:37,933
原来连我吃饭这件事
So even the act of eating

221
00:07:38,033 --> 00:07:39,400
都被别人控制了
Was being controlled by someone else

222
00:07:39,533 --> 00:07:41,400
这就是盐的第三层秘密
This is the third secret of salt

223
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,166
它不只是一种经济品
It is not just an economic good

224
00:07:43,333 --> 00:07:44,800
它还是一种共识品
It is a consensus good

225
00:07:44,966 --> 00:07:46,333
越普通的东西
The more ordinary something is

226
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:49,166
越容易让所有人形成共同感受
The easier it is for everyone to share a common feeling

227
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:51,233
你被一个高端奢侈品收割
If you get exploited by a luxury brand

228
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:52,433
别人可能没感觉
Others might not feel it

229
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:55,400
但你被米 盐 水 电 房租 通讯费收割
But if you get exploited by rice salt water electricity rent phone bills

230
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,600
所有人都会感到痛
Everyone feels the pain

231
00:07:57,733 --> 00:07:59,566
因为这些东西不分阶层
Because these things do not discriminate by class

232
00:07:59,966 --> 00:08:01,166
穷人要用
Poor people need them

233
00:08:01,533 --> 00:08:02,733
富人也要用
Rich people need them too

234
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:05,233
只是穷人的痛感更强
It is just that poor people feel the pain more

235
00:08:05,433 --> 00:08:07,600
所以盐能成为反抗的符号
So salt could become a symbol of resistance

236
00:08:07,766 --> 00:08:08,800
不是因为它贵
Not because it was expensive

237
00:08:08,966 --> 00:08:11,200
而是因为它把抽象的不公平
But because it turned abstract injustice

238
00:08:11,233 --> 00:08:13,633
变成了每个人舌尖上的感觉
Into something everyone could taste

239
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,566
这里有一个很重要的认知
Here is an important insight

240
00:08:15,733 --> 00:08:18,700
普通人反感的往往不是付钱
What ordinary people resent is usually not paying

241
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:20,200
而是没得选
It is having no choice

242
00:08:20,366 --> 00:08:23,233
如果你觉得一件东西贵你可能会忍
If you think something is expensive you might endure it

243
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:25,433
但如果你发现自己根本没有选择权
But if you realize you have no choice at all

244
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:26,633
你会生气
You get angry

245
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:29,700
这也是今天很多商业模式翻车的原因
This is also why many business models crash today

246
00:08:29,966 --> 00:08:31,133
会员自动续费
Auto renewing subscriptions

247
00:08:31,233 --> 00:08:32,500
大数据杀熟
Algorithmic price discrimination

248
00:08:32,633 --> 00:08:34,166
平台抽成越来越高
Platforms taking bigger and bigger cuts

249
00:08:34,366 --> 00:08:36,433
外卖商家被平台绑住
Takeout merchants tied to platforms

250
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:38,800
创作者被流量规则绑住
Creators tied to traffic rules

251
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,100
用户一边用一边骂
Users complain while still using them

252
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:42,166
为什么
Why

253
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,433
不是因为大家不愿意付费
Not because people do not want to pay

254
00:08:44,566 --> 00:08:47,200
而是因为入口被控制以后
But because once the gateway is controlled

255
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:49,000
选择权越来越少
Choice keeps shrinking

256
00:08:49,166 --> 00:08:52,233
当一个系统既离不开又说不清
When a system is indispensable opaque

257
00:08:52,366 --> 00:08:53,366
还绕不过
And impossible to bypass

258
00:08:53,766 --> 00:08:56,533
它就会从便利变成压迫
It goes from being convenient to being oppressive

259
00:08:56,766 --> 00:08:58,566
盐的故事提醒我们
The story of salt reminds us

260
00:08:58,766 --> 00:09:01,733
任何入口生意都有一条危险边界
Any gateway business has a dangerous boundary

261
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:03,100
它可以收费
It can charge

262
00:09:03,233 --> 00:09:05,566
但不能让人觉得自己被关起来
But it cannot make people feel locked up

263
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:06,966
它可以赚钱
It can make money

264
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:09,433
但不能让人觉得自己没有退路
But it cannot make people feel trapped

265
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:12,833
真正高级的商业不是把人锁死
Truly great business is not about locking people in

266
00:09:12,966 --> 00:09:16,833
而是让人明知道可以走却愿意留下
It is about making people willing to stay even when they know they can leave

267
00:09:16,966 --> 00:09:19,200
讲到这里你可能会问
At this point you might ask

268
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:22,433
盐的故事跟我今天有什么关系
What does the story of salt have to do with me today

269
00:09:22,566 --> 00:09:23,500
关系很大
A lot

270
00:09:23,733 --> 00:09:25,566
因为每个时代都有自己的盐
Because every era has its own salt

271
00:09:25,733 --> 00:09:29,000
古代的盐是身体离不开的刚需
In ancient times salt was a necessity the body could not do without

272
00:09:29,166 --> 00:09:32,833
工业时代的电是机器离不开的刚需
In the industrial age electricity was a necessity machines could not do without

273
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,400
互联网时代的流量
In the internet age traffic

274
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:36,533
是生意离不开的刚需
Was a necessity businesses could not do without

275
00:09:36,633 --> 00:09:38,166
AI 时代的新盐
The new salt in the AI era

276
00:09:38,366 --> 00:09:40,566
可能是算力 模型 数据 接口
Might be computing power models data APIs

277
00:09:40,566 --> 00:09:44,633
也可能是你每天用来提问和做决策的那个入口
Or it might be that gateway you use every day to ask questions and make decisions

278
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:47,000
你今天问 AI 写方案
Today you ask AI to write proposals

279
00:09:47,166 --> 00:09:48,966
明天让 AI 做表格
Tomorrow you let AI make spreadsheets

280
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:51,733
后天让 AI 帮你判断要不要买一个东西
The day after you let AI help you decide whether to buy something

281
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,766
慢慢地你会发现
Gradually you will find

282
00:09:53,933 --> 00:09:55,433
它不再只是工具
It is no longer just a tool

283
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,500
它开始变成你的思考入口
It starts becoming your gateway for thinking

284
00:09:57,733 --> 00:09:59,600
当一个工具变成入口
When a tool becomes a gateway

285
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,733
它的商业逻辑就变了
Its business logic changes

286
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:03,333
早期它会很便宜
Early on it will be very cheap

287
00:10:03,633 --> 00:10:04,600
甚至免费
Even free

288
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,733
因为它要培养你的习惯
Because it needs to build your habits

289
00:10:06,933 --> 00:10:10,166
等你离不开它它才有真正的定价权
Only when you cannot leave it does it gain real pricing power

290
00:10:10,433 --> 00:10:11,566
这和盐很像
This is a lot like salt

291
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:13,833
一开始你觉得只是加一点味道
At first you think it just adds a little flavor

292
00:10:13,966 --> 00:10:16,333
后来你发现每顿饭都少不了它
Later you realize you cannot have a meal without it

293
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:18,000
AI 产品也是这样
AI products are the same

294
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:20,333
今天你觉得只是帮你省时间
Today you think it just saves you time

295
00:10:20,533 --> 00:10:24,833
以后它可能会影响你怎么学习 怎么工作 怎么做决定
Later it might affect how you learn work and make decisions

296
00:10:25,033 --> 00:10:27,133
所以普通人真正要学的
So what ordinary people really need to learn

297
00:10:27,133 --> 00:10:29,233
不是每天追哪个模型更强
Is not which model is stronger every day

298
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:30,966
而是学会识别
But to learn to recognize

299
00:10:31,166 --> 00:10:33,366
谁在掌握新的入口
Who is controlling the new gateway

300
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,333
谁在掌握新的盐
Who is controlling the new salt

301
00:10:35,433 --> 00:10:37,100
你可以问自己三个问题
You can ask yourself three questions

302
00:10:37,433 --> 00:10:39,533
第一这个东西是不是高频
First is this thing high frequency

303
00:10:39,766 --> 00:10:41,533
我是不是每天都用
Do I use it every day

304
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:44,133
第二这个东西是不是刚需
Second is this thing essential

305
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:47,600
不用它我的效率是不是明显下降
Without it does my efficiency obviously drop

306
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:50,566
第三这个东西是不是低替代
Third is this thing hard to substitute

307
00:10:50,766 --> 00:10:52,933
我换掉它的成本是不是越来越高
Is the cost of switching higher and higher

308
00:10:53,133 --> 00:10:55,033
只要三个答案都是是
If all three answers are yes

309
00:10:55,166 --> 00:10:56,366
你就要警惕
You should be alert

310
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,833
它正在从工具变成基础设施
It is going from being a tool to being infrastructure

311
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,300
对普通人来说
For ordinary people

312
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:03,366
最好的策略不是拒绝它
The best strategy is not to reject it

313
00:11:03,566 --> 00:11:06,533
拒绝盐的人最后吃饭没味道
People who rejected salt ended up with tasteless food

314
00:11:06,766 --> 00:11:10,433
拒绝 AI 的人未来工作会很吃力
People who reject AI will struggle to work in the future

315
00:11:10,633 --> 00:11:12,300
但你也不能完全依赖它
But you cannot depend on it entirely either

316
00:11:12,433 --> 00:11:13,800
完全依赖一个入口
Depending entirely on one gateway

317
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,833
就等于把自己的选择权交出去
Means handing over your power of choice

318
00:11:15,933 --> 00:11:17,000
你可以用它
You can use it

319
00:11:17,133 --> 00:11:18,900
但要保留迁移能力
But keep the ability to migrate

320
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:20,300
你可以订阅它
You can subscribe to it

321
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:22,166
但要知道替代方案
But know the alternatives

322
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:24,133
你可以让 AI 帮你写
You can let AI help you write

323
00:11:24,233 --> 00:11:26,000
但不能让 AI 替你判断
But you cannot let AI judge for you

324
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:29,366
因为真正值钱的从来不是盐本身
Because what is truly valuable is never the salt itself

325
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:33,000
而是谁掌握了盐从哪里来卖给谁
But who controls where the salt comes from and who it is sold to

326
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,366
按什么规则卖
And under what rules

327
00:11:34,566 --> 00:11:35,833
回到开头那袋盐
Back to that bag of salt from the beginning

328
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:36,800
它便宜
It is cheap

329
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:37,900
安静
Quiet

330
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:38,833
不起眼
Unremarkable

331
00:11:39,033 --> 00:11:42,166
但它让我们看见一个很残酷的真相
But it reveals a brutal truth

332
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:44,100
世界上最强的控制
The strongest control in the world

333
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:46,833
往往不是控制你一年买一次的东西
Is usually not controlling what you buy once a year

334
00:11:47,033 --> 00:11:49,700
而是控制你每天都离不开的东西
But controlling what you cannot live without every day

335
00:11:49,900 --> 00:11:52,766
所以下次你在厨房里撒盐的时候
So next time you sprinkle salt in your kitchen

336
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:54,033
可以想一想
You might want to think

337
00:11:54,233 --> 00:11:57,833
这袋几块钱的盐曾经让帝国续命
This bag of salt costing a few yuan once kept empires alive

338
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,833
也曾经让普通人反抗
And once made ordinary people rise up

339
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:02,133
它提醒你的不是怎么炒菜
It does not remind you how to cook

340
00:12:02,366 --> 00:12:04,933
而是怎么识别这个世界真正的入口
But how to recognize the real gateways of this world

341
00:12:05,133 --> 00:12:07,566
谁控制入口谁就控制价格
Whoever controls the gateway controls the price

342
00:12:07,733 --> 00:12:11,000
谁控制刚需谁就控制选择
Whoever controls the necessity controls the choice

343
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,533
谁能看懂盐
Whoever can read salt

344
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:15,200
谁就能看懂一个时代的财富流向
Can read the flow of wealth in an era
